definition.value: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is podophyllotoxin in which the methyl ether group at position 4 of the trimethoxyphenyl group has been cleaved to afford the corresponding phenol.
A chlorocarbon that is tetrachloro substituted ethene.
A hexaric acid derived by oxidation of sugar such as glucose with nitric acid.
A pyrazoloquinoline that is 2,5-dihydropyrazolo[4,3-c]quinolin-3-one which is substituted at position 2 by a 5-butyl-2-thienyl group.
